args: I had a dream that I killed Ulthar.\nAnd when I awoke, he was dead.
I'm scared. Oh my savior, help me!\nI fear terrible things are to come.
*sniff* Is it my fault he's dead? Is it?
Another stray. Are you Ulthar's friend?\nOh, I'm so sorry, little kitty,\nbut Ulthar is...
Are you trying to cheer me up?\n*sniff* Thank you.
But you shouldn't get too close to me.\nIf you do...
No. That was a dream. It must have been.
Anyway, I'm going to leave now.\nLet's play again sometime, kitty.
Offering. Oblation. Wailing falsehood. \nTo whom does your life belong?\nWho holds dominion on your light?
Submit yourself. Capitulate.\nProffer your being to the feast.
Why does every cat I meet die?!\nIt can't be me! It can't!
Offer yourself unto the Ancient One.
It really is my fault. The me that isn't me\nis killing everyone and everything.
What should I do? What CAN I do?
Save me! Forgive me in your great mercy!
First the cats die, and then the people.\nBut I don't want to die! I want to live!

I know your true name. Yes, I know it well.
O bizarre messenger! Disciple of salvation
who is the guide of all! Grant this poor old
woman your mercy, I beg of you!
No salvation to its seekers.\nForgiveness the errand of a fool.\nDesire is heard solely by the void.
We are Chaos. Messenger of the One.\nYou, a fool who seeks the One's feast.\nNow proffer yourself unto Us.
W-was that a dream, too?\nDid I just KILL someone?!
Sh-she's dead! Her neck is...\nOh, but this is horrible!
Was that...me? Or the me that is not me?
We are Chaos. Messenger of the One.\nYou, a fool who seeks the One's feast.\nNow proffer yourself unto Us.
